    <text>
        <body>
            <pb n="1R"/>
            <p rend="align(right)">
                <placeName>New Orleans</placeName>
                <date>March 18th<add>?</add> 1854</date>
            </p>
            <p>
                <addressee>Revd Isaac Leeser</addressee>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(2)">Dr Sir</p>
            <p>I am happy to inform you the Brig <add>?</add><lb/> Mallory has duly arrived &amp;
                one case now<lb/> in store I am busy <sic>makeing</sic> out the lists<lb/> of the
                respective names &amp; the books to be sent<lb/> them &amp; at same time informing
                them of the<lb/> Books being now ready for delivery &amp; shall<lb/> also as soon as
                the other case comes up<lb/> endeavour forwarding to <persName>Mr
                    Osterman</persName><lb/> the Books named. <persName>John Marks</persName> now
                resides<lb/> in <placeName>New York</placeName>
                <persName>M. Barnett</persName> is residing in<lb/>
                <placeName>San Francisco</placeName> (<persName>Hirshfield</persName> in
                    <placeName>New York</placeName><lb/> is his Partner) <persName>Elias
                    Newburger</persName> is<lb/> yet here but also about leaving &amp; I doubt<lb/>
                if he is <hi rend="underline">that Be<add>?</add></hi> to take the work he
                    <sic>orderd</sic><lb/> I shall however try him <persName>Dr I L
                        Craucow<add>?</add></persName> I<lb/> think will take the Books &amp;
                    <persName>Rodriguez </persName>also<lb/> I will do all I can do &amp; as soon as
                I<lb/> obtain any funds send it to you</p>
            <p>The Hebrew Ball of the Hebrew Benevolent<lb/> association came off last night it was
                a<lb/> brilliant affair well attended I have no<lb/> Doubt a Handsome sum will have
                been<lb/> made. My time is at the disposal of another &amp; of course<lb/> I cannot
                devote that time to private correspondence</p>
            <pb n="1V"/>
            <p>that I could wish still I shall strive not<lb/> to neglect your Interest if I
                neglect<lb/> all others</p>
            <p rend="indent(7)">Yours Very Truly</p>
            <p rend="indent(7)">
                <persName role="author">Isaac Hart</persName>
            </p>
            <p>I am sorry you did not have any name or<lb/> one of the Handsome Bibles.</p>
            <p>I must not omit to congratulate you on<lb/> the style &amp; finish of this book. It
                could<lb/> not be excell'd &amp; is sure to please</p>
        </body>
